;; tatara 鑪 — seed global manufacturing-plant + logistics graph (ADR-2606171800)
;; ============================================================================
;; A BOUNDED, :representative illustrative seed — NOT exhaustive coverage. Every node is
;; tagged :representative (G5). Coordinates are ROUNDED to ~0.01° (city / campus scale, G1)
;; and figures (headcount / floor area / capacity) are disclosed-or-estimated round numbers,
;; NOT live telemetry. Absence of a plant means "not yet ingested", never "does not exist".
;;
;; :plant/operator joins kabuto org.corp.* — a COMPANY, never a person (G4).
;; :plant/headcount-est is the AGGREGATE disclosed facility-employment figure (a SIZE, like
;; market-cap) — there is NO :worker/* / :person/* attribute anywhere; an individual worker
;; is STRUCTURALLY UNREPRESENTABLE (see ontology header; mirrors sarutahiko/itonami/niyaku G2).
;;
;; :flow/via reuses the watari :lane/chokepoint + watatsuna :station/chokepoint keywords
;; (:malacca :luzon-strait :suez-red-sea :gibraltar :panama …) so plant export-dependence
;; composes with live vessel transit (watari) and static cable load (watatsuna) into ONE
;; maritime resilience picture — routed to redundancy / reshoring, NEVER to interdiction.
;; ============================================================================

